To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Maryland Public Information Act, I hereby request the following records for every sworn officer and civilian member of the Howard County Police Department for fiscal year 2022:
1. First and last name;
2. Unique sequence number;
3. Race;
4. Gender;
5. Hire date;
6. 2022 salary;
7. 2022 overtime

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request.  Alternatively, please consider waiving any fees, pursuant to § 4-206(e)(2)(ii) of the General Provisions Article, as this request is on behalf of individuals served by the Maryland Office of the Public Defender, a state government agency, which solely serves indigent citizens of Maryland.  As a result, my request for the above-listed public records is in the public interest. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Deborah Levi
Director of Special Litigation
Maryland Office of the Public Defender
(443) 272-1068

Good afternoon Ms. Levi,

In response to your Maryland Public Information Act request for, "Records for every sworn officer and civilian member of the Howard County Police Department for fiscal year 2022:

  1.  First and last name;
  2.  Unique sequence number;
  3.  Race;
  4.  Gender;
  5.  Hire Date;
  6.  2022 salary;
  7.  2022 overtime"

Please find the attached responsive records for items #1 through #5. We are in need of clarification for item #6 2022 salary. When you are asking for salary, are you asking for their annual base salary or what they were actually paid in fiscal year 2022? Once we receive clarification for item #6, we will be able to provide items #6 and #7.
Best,
Sarah Allison
Howard County Police Department

